Exact copies of material already on TPB should be deleted.  Like this one.  It just clutters the place up and wastes our DL bandwidth/cap and time.

I tend to agree, BT most times the original loader (e.g. 26k) could do two things:

1. Use better filters to make the copy as good as possible (instead of just posting it asap), and 

2. Make it smaller. There is no discernable diff. between a 2GB file and a 1GB file (at e.g. 720x288). 

Then, so many people wouldn't be trying to incrementally improve it.

Keep in mind that if a specific torrent was released by only one uploader for the sake of bandwidth and simplicity, investigating and prosecuting authorities would have a very easy time tracking IPs of all seeders that have that torrent simply because it would only be limitted to one release of a torrent.

Pros and Cons either way.
